# Zero-Trust & Data Protection Rules
- **No Hardcoded Secrets**: NEVER commit API keys, tokens, or passwords. Use [GCP Secret Manager](mdc:https://cloud.google.com/secret-manager) references.
- **Least Privilege**: Any new code or skill must request the absolute minimum permissions required.
- **Data Encryption**: All data at rest must be encrypted (SC-28). All data in transit must use TLS 1.3+ (SC-8).
- **HITL Enforcement**: No remediation actions can be performed without a documented human approval in the audit trail.
- **Audit Logging**: Every action taken by the Agent must be logged to a tamper-proof audit log (AU-2).